<doc id="512061" wikidata="Q1535185" url="?curid=512061" title="8th Golden Raspberry Awards">
<text>The 8th Golden Raspberry Awards were held on April 10, 1988, at the Hollywood Roosevelt Hotel to recognize the worst the film industry had to offer in 1987. &quot;Leonard Part 6&quot; was the biggest &quot;winner&quot; with three awards out of five nominations. Although he did not attend the ceremony, actor/producer/co-writer Bill Cosby later accepted all his awards on &quot;The Late Show&quot;. This marked the only time Cosby &quot;earned&quot; a Razzie prior to the sexual assault allegations levied against him in October 16, 2014, which besmirched his career and legacy.

